* Upload unstructured (text) overall results to RaceRoster.
*   Param 1 (%1):  The RaceRoster sub-event ID.
*   Param 2 (%2):  The destination filename (must start with ~, e.g. ~results_5k.txt)
*
*   Recommendation:
*     - Define sub-event IDs in Entries.INI (e.g. %rr_5k_u%) rather than hardcoding
*       them here or in multiple listings — one place to update when IDs change.
*     - If you also publish structured results, use a separate ID for unstructured
*       (e.g. %rr_5k% for structured, %rr_5k_u% for unstructured).
*     - The ~ prefix on the destination filename is required. It creates the upload
*       file in the race directory; without ~, the file is created in the binary
*       directory, which can cause issues when switching races.

Output Format       txt
External Report To  RaceRoster
Destination         %2
Records Per Page    100000
No Page Numbers
List DNF
Dq Field            DNF

Header
.INCLUDE            RACENAME
##%1##
.End of Header

Select              BIB
>                   0
And
Select              DNF
EQ
Field               BIB
Field               Name
Field               Sex
Field               AGE
Field               DIV
Field               City
Field               State
Field               DIVPLACE
Field               DIVTOTAL
Field               SEXPLACE
Field               SEXTOTAL

Event               Finish
minus               GunStart
Time Format         H:MM:SS.01
Field Header        Gun Time

Event               Finish
minus               ChipStart
Time Format         H:MM:SS.01
Field Header        Chip Time
